       Name: Solar Censure
       Kind: Spell
     Target: TAR_CHAR_OFFENSIVE
   Position: POS_FIGHTING
   Min Mana: 17
 Wait Beats: 12
 Can Learn: TRUE
Noun Damage: solar censure
   Wear-Off: !Solar Censure!
Acquisition:
   - Cleric: level 40
Description:
   Solar Censure is a mid-level Cleric offensive spell invoking Disk's solar
   aspect to censure a transgressor. The Cleric formally condemns the target
   in Disk's name and channels solar divine energy as a focused bolt of
   radiant judgment. The spell deals significant holy damage and carries
   the weight of divine disapproval.

   Solar Censure is the Cleric's strongest single-target offensive spell
   before reaching the tier of Flamestrike and Disk's Word. It is more
   powerful than Divine Strike and serves as the Cleric's primary offensive
   tool in the mid-career range. The censure aspect of the spell means it
   is particularly effective against targets who have committed transgressions
   that Disk has noted — repeat offenders take increased damage.
*******************************************************************************
